name: Brie
description: Soft cow's milk cheese from Brie, France. Pale with slight gray under white mold. Creamy flavor, popular worldwide.

name: Cheddar
description: Hard, off-white, sharp-tasting natural cheese. Originated in English village of Cheddar in Somerset.

name: Gouda
description: Mild, yellow cheese from cow's milk. Popular worldwide for rich, creamy texture and slightly sweet flavor.

name: Blue
description: General classification of cheeses with blue mold, spotted or veined. Distinct, tangy taste.

name: Mozzarella
description: Italian cheese from buffalo's milk. Received Traditional Specialities Guaranteed certification from EU.
